e LiveStore per process lifetime.; Session entity: :task/t-c8e2ef76; Session entity: :recon/trace-3fe4a183cfca33e4; Session entity: :recon/trace-c2af3decdd80b596; Session entity: :recon/trace-6393d4fa1037d8d0; Session entity: :task/t-0f2f8d26; Session entity: :task/t-57e2f282; Session entity: :task/t-bf2cc769; Session entity: :recon/trace-edf164920b53bc89; Session entity: :recon/trace-58d0fbecc7cba363; Session entity: :recon/trace-c7b1e5eb8170e2a5; Session entity: :recon/trace-4048832a590998b8; Session entity: :task/t-5360aa51; Session entity: :task/t-e49591fe; Session entity: :recon/trace-a8f9632efc4da03f; Session entity: :recon/trace-4ce92eb267733ac5; Session entity: :task/t-cf2b0073; Session entity: :task/t-cc17e709; Session entity: :recon/trace-5f0b0dd2c7d55a27; Session entity: :task/t-7a1e8dc0; Session entity: :task/t-2144c331; Session entity: :task/t-e959becd; Session entity: :task/t-9873f31f; Session entity: :recon/trace-5a33753e34f85520; Session entity: :config/concept-sigmoid-temperature; Session entity: :task/t-dcbc1d54; Session entity: :config/calibration-similarity-count; Session entity: :recon/trace-6b41bf184eca7512; Session entity: :config/calibration-similarity-sum; Session entity: :task/t-c1b0c212; Session entity: :task/t-15b0117d; Session entity: :task/t-ae6a8d4b; Session entity: :recon/trace-38ccd66c1438698b\nAUDIT-LOOP-2: Learning Loop 2 (Structure Discovery/OBSERVER-5) is entirely open -- deepest missing piece. Observation: NOT IMPLEMENTED -- no code records access patterns, temporal co-occurrence, or co-modification data as datoms. Analysis: NOT IMPLEMENTED -- no code detects temporal coupling patterns or discovers latent boundaries. Feedback: NOT IMPLEMENTED -- no code proposes new boundary definitions. The topology module coupling analysis is the closest code but operates on static file sets for agent coordination, not temporal observation patterns. SOLUTION: Implement in 3 phases: (1) Observation: instrument store queries and command invocations to record access patterns as datoms (which entities accessed together, how often, in what sequence). (2) Analysis: periodic scan of access patterns for temporal coupling (entities that co-occur above threshold). (3) Feedback: when coupling persists across N sessions, propose new boundary definition connecting the coupled entity sets. JUSTIFICATION: The boundary set is currently static -- defined at init, never refined. For self-calibrating vision, boundary discovery is essential. VERIFICATION: Synthetic test: create access patterns with known clustering, verify boundary proposals match. DEPENDENCIES: This is the deepest missing piece. Independent of other audit findings but requires AUDIT-C8-7 (dynamic boundaries) to accept the proposed boundaries.; PERF Layer 2: 20 full O(N) datom scans in single braid status. Hottest: telemetry_from_store (10 scans), methodology_gaps cascade (crystallization_candidates + all_tasks + witness_gaps + spec_concentration), entities_matching_pattern (7x per fitness), all_tasks called 4x redundantly. Total: ~2.16M datom iterations at 108K datoms. Fix: use attribute_index, cache results, materialize in views.; AUDIT-EXT COVERAGE-BUG (from PROJECT_ASSESSMENT Priority 3): Coverage computation inflated by phantom spec references. PROBLEM: bilateral.rs compute_depth_weighted_coverage() counts :impl/implements refs as coverage even if the referenced spec entity has been retracted or doesn't appear in the LIVE projection. This inflates F(S)'s C component. The 142 spec-impl gaps may be undercounted — some 'covered' specs may be covered by phantom references to retracted entities. JUSTIFICATION: If C is inflated, F(S) is inflated, and the saw-tooth model can't be validated. Measurement integrity is a prerequisite for all convergence analysis. C6 (falsifiability) should apply to the measurement system itself — the coverage metric should be falsifiable, and currently it isn't because phantom references can't be detected. SOLUTION: Intersect :impl/implements refs with live spec projection before counting coverage. Only count refs that point to entities present in the LIVE view with :spec/element-type. Small fix: <50 lines. VERIFICATION: Create a spec element, add impl link, retract the spec element. Coverage should NOT count the link. DEPENDENCIES: Independent. Small fix with high measurement impact. Affects interpretation of F(S) and the verification sprint results. FILES: crates/braid-kernel/src/bilateral.rs. SEVERITY: High. WAVE: 1. EFFORT: 2h.; MINOR-4: bootstrap.rs and trace.rs in CLI crate are application-layer DDIS code [MEDIUM, from FULL_AUDIT F-ARCH-003]. bootstrap.rs (1046 LOC) parses spec/*.md for INV/ADR/NEG patterns — DDIS-specific format. trace.rs (1464 LOC) scans Rust source for INV-/ADR-/NEG- patterns — DDIS methodology. Both are in braid CLI crate not kernel, so kernel C8 boundary is maintained. But they violate C8 at system level. SOLUTION: When plugin/extractor framework matures, move to a braid-ddis plugin crate. For now: acceptable layering for Stage 0-1 where DDIS is the only policy. VERIFICATION: When migrated, bootstrap.rs and trace.rs are in separate crate. DEPENDENCIES: Part of longer-term C8 migration (Wave 5 in FULL_AUDIT roadmap). ~8 hours when needed.; AUDIT-EXT PERF-SCANS (from AUDIT_REPORT): 82 full-datom-scan call sites across 18 files — O(N) patterns that will dominate at 500K+ datoms. PROBLEM: 82 call sites perform full O(N) scans over the datom set. At 108K datoms with ~80ms status time, each scan costs ~1ms. At 500K datoms, these accumulate to 250ms-1s. At 1M datoms, 1-5s. Top offenders: entities_matching_pattern() called during fitness computation (756K datom iterations per status call), all_tasks() called 4x per status, concept_observation_coverage() full scan where attribute_index would give O(K), CC-2 existence check using .any() over all datoms, Frontier::at() full scan for time-travel. JUSTIFICATION: The secondary indexes (entity_index, attribute_index, avet_index) exist precisely to avoid full scans. Most of these 82 call sites could use an index lookup instead. The pattern suggests the indexes were added after the scan-based code was written, and the scan-based code was never migrated. SOLUTION: Migrate the top 20 full-scan call sites to use index lookups. Prioritize by frequency: status path first (called every command), then fitness computation, then bilateral scans. VERIFICATION: braid status on 500K-datom store takes <500ms. DEPENDENCIES: Complements F-PERF-001 (merge rebuild). Both are O(N) elimination tasks. FILES: 18 files across kernel and CLI. SEVERITY: Medium. WAVE: 4. EFFORT: 16h.; AUDIT-ARCH-1: Four circular dependency cycles in kernel production code. (1) store <-> merge [HIGH]: store imports merge::run_cascade/CascadeReceipt; merge imports store::Frontier/MergeReceipt/Store. Neither module can be independently tested. Fix: extract shared types (Frontier, MergeReceipt, CascadeReceipt) to types.rs. (2) store <-> bilateral [MEDIUM]: store.rs calls crate::bilateral::FitnessScore/FitnessComponents/weights via inline paths; bilateral imports Store. The core data structure depends on fitness scoring. Fix: extract FitnessScore/FitnessComponents/weight constants to fitness.rs. (3) routing <-> context [MEDIUM]: routing imports context::ActionCategory/GuidanceAction; context imports routing::*. These are conceptually one module. Fix: merge them or extract shared types. (4) proptest_strategies <-> bilateral [LOW]: proptest imports bilateral::FitnessComponents in production; bilateral imports proptest only in cfg(test). Fix: move arb_fitness_* into bilateral test module. VERIFICATION: After each fix, verify cargo check passes with no circular use warnings. Verify tests pass. DEPENDENCIES: Cycle 2 (store-bilateral) interacts with AUDIT-SOUND-2 (F(S) redesign) -- extracting fitness types is a prerequisite for F(S) changes.; PERF-EXT-1: Datom cloned 5-7x into indexes — estimated 100-250 MB RAM for 108K datoms [P1-HIGH, from AUDIT_REPORT PERF-008]. Each Datom is stored once in the primary BTreeSet, then cloned into entity_index, attribute_index, vaet_index, avet_index, and potentially live_view. With Entity (32 bytes) + Attribute (~50 bytes avg) + Value (variable) + TxId (32 bytes) + Op (1 byte), each datom is ~120-200 bytes. At 108K datoms with 5-7 copies each, estimated memory: 100-250 MB. With index-by-offset (store indices as references or offsets into the primary set instead of clones), estimated: 25-55 MB (4-5x reduction). SOLUTION: Replace cloned Datom storage in indexes with offsets or references into the primary BTreeSet. Each index entry stores a reference/key into the primary set instead of a full copy. Arena allocation could also work. VERIFICATION: Benchmark memory usage before/after. Target: less than 50 MB for 108K datoms. DEPENDENCIES: Independent but significant refactor. Should be done after CORR-3 (index path unification) since changing index representation requires touching all index code anyway.; AUDIT-SPEC-006: Witness challenge cognitive independence is architectural, not mechanically enforced. PROBLEM: witness.rs challenge execution happens within the same process context. No subagent spawning. The 6-level challenge protocol runs all levels within a single call. INV-WITNESS-009/010 require decorrelated multi-verdict from cognitively independent contexts. The spec warns: 'three API calls to the same model within the same conversation context are NOT decorrelated.' Current implementation has this exact pattern. SOLUTION: Stage 1-2. When subagent infrastructure (topology.rs) matures, wire challenge evaluation to spawn independent Agent contexts per INV-TOPOLOGY-003. Each challenge level runs in a separate context with no shared state. VERIFICATION: Challenge verdicts show statistical independence across levels (chi-squared test on verdict distribution). DEPENDS-ON: Stage 2 (topology/coordination infrastructure). INTERACTS-WITH: W1-002 (topology parameterization).; AUDIT-CORR-001: Four expect() calls in production code should be converted to Result propagation or documented as provably-safe. Locations: store.rs:193 'committed transactions always have a tx_id' (typestate guarantees this — safe), store.rs:1418 'TxId serialization cannot fail' (serde_json on primitive types — effectively infallible), resolution.rs:193/195 'Value serialization cannot fail' (same), resolution.rs:199 'active is non-empty' (guarded by early return — safe). SOLUTION: For typestate-guarded cases, add // SAFETY: typestate guarantees Some. For serde_json cases, consider .unwrap_or_else(|e| unreachable!('...: {e}')) for explicit documentation. VERIFICATION: All expect() in kernel production code have accompanying safety proofs. DEPENDS-ON: None. INTERACTS-WITH: None.; AUDIT-ARCH-2: Eight god modules exceed 4000 LOC -- decomposition needed. (1) guidance.rs 7119 LOC: extract telemetry/scoring subsystem. (2) store.rs 5944 LOC: extract StatusSnapshot + FitnessGradient to snapshot.rs. (3) concept.rs 5362 LOC: split extraction vs linking into concept/extraction.rs and concept/linking.rs. (4) seed.rs 5314 LOC: split assembly vs formatting. (5) schema.rs 4957 LOC: C8 fix (AUDIT-C8-1) eliminates ~2K LOC by moving L1-L5 to policy. (6) bilateral.rs 4769 LOC: split F(S) components vs cycle orchestration. (7) harvest.rs 4433 LOC: extract text analysis heuristics to utility module. (8) query/graph.rs 4546 LOC: strong candidate for separate braid-graph crate -- 20+ algorithms (PageRank, Fiedler, Cheeger, HITS, k-core, persistent homology) that are general-purpose graph computations, not braid-specific. VERIFICATION: After each decomposition, verify: cargo check passes, all tests pass, no API changes to public surface. DEPENDENCIES: schema.rs decomposition depends on AUDIT-C8-1 (L1+L2 migration). store.rs decomposition depends on AUDIT-ARCH-1 (circular dep fix). Others are independent.; AUDIT-EXT CRITICAL-1 (from AUDIT_REPORT): Coherence gate not wired into write path — 99%+ of store mutations bypass contradiction prevention. PROBLEM: The coherence gate (coherence.rs, 1,300 LOC, 18 tests) is well-tested library code but architecturally disconnected from the CLI write path. LiveStore::write_tx() calls store.apply_datoms() directly, bypassing both schema validation and coherence checking. The only production caller of transact_with_coherence() is proposal.rs:468. Every CLI command (observe, write assert, task create, harvest, spec create) bypasses coherence checking entirely. JUSTIFICATION: The coherence gate is the system's primary mechanism for preventing contradictions from entering the store. Without it, every other formal guarantee is undermined — the store can accumulate contradictions unchecked, making INV-COHERENCE-* vacuously true (never tested against real transactions). This is a ~20-line fix with the highest ROI of any finding across all four audits. SOLUTION: Wire transact_with_coherence() into LiveStore::write_tx() as a pre-check. If coherence check fails, return error with recovery hint. VERIFICATION: After fix, manually inject a contradictory assertion and verify it is rejected. DEPENDENCIES: Independent. No prerequisites. Should be the FIRST fix applied. Complements F-INV-001 (LIVE view correctness) — both affect store integrity. FINDING SOURCE: AUDIT_REPORT.md Section 2.2 CRITICAL-1, confirmed by FORMAL_SOUNDNESS_AUDIT_REPORT.md. My FULL_AUDIT missed this entirely. FILES: crates/braid/src/live_store.rs, crates/braid-kernel/src/coherence.rs, crates/braid-kernel/src/store.rs. SEVERITY: Critical. WAVE: 0. EFFORT: 1h.; MINOR-1: Stateright model has 1 ignored test — transact_coherence_no_undetected_contradictions [LOW, from FULL_AUDIT F-FORMAL-002]. 10 passing stateright tests, 1 ignored. Reason for skip not documented. May cover unimplemented INV-COHERENCE-002 (no undetected contradictions) or may be intermittently failing. Either way, ignored test is a coverage gap. SOLUTION: Investigate and either fix the test or document skip reason with a todo linking to the relevant task. VERIFICATION: Test passes or has documented skip. DEPENDENCIES: Related to AUDIT-SOUND-1 (coherence gate) — if coherence gate is wired, this test may start passing.; AUDIT-TYPE-005: SchemaError::Inconsistency(String) catch-all should be split into specific variants. PROBLEM: error.rs:148 maps all schema consistency violations to one variant. Cannot distinguish duplicate attribute definitions from type conflicts from cardinality mismatches. The string message is the only discriminant. SOLUTION: Split into DuplicateAttribute { attr }, TypeConflict { attr, expected, got }, CardinalityMismatch { attr, expected, got }. VERIFICATION: SchemaError has no Inconsistency(String) variant. DEPENDS-ON: None. INTERACTS-WITH: W2-004 (validate_evolution produces schema errors).; AUDIT-MISC-2: Minor graph algorithm numerical edge cases. (1) Cheeger constant (graph.rs:2385-2388, 2424-2427) uses .partial_cmp().unwrap() on Fiedler vector components -- panics on NaN. Cannot trigger with current unweighted graph API but fragile if weighted edges added. (2) Kirchhoff index (graph.rs:888-906) does not clamp negative eigenvalue artifacts from Jacobi iteration -- could produce incorrect/negative indices in degenerate cases. (3) Jacobi eigendecomposition (graph.rs:397-461) has max_sweeps=50 with no non-convergence warning -- silently returns approximate eigenvalues. (4) Aggregation COUNT on empty result returns empty Rel not COUNT=0 row (different from SQL semantics). (5) SUM/AVG silently skip non-numeric values. (6) GROUP BY key uses lossy string representation. SOLUTION: Add convergence check to Jacobi (warn if max_sweeps reached). Replace unwrap with unwrap_or for Cheeger. Clamp negative eigenvalues in Kirchhoff. Document aggregation semantics. VERIFICATION: Unit tests with degenerate inputs: empty graph, single node, NaN injection (for Cheeger). DEPENDENCIES: Independent. Low priority.; AUDIT-MISC-1: Transaction Applied typestate is