al scan that detects spec-impl gaps, store contains signal datoms with :signal/type structural. braid query can retrieve signal history. DEPENDENCIES: Prerequisite for AUDIT-COH-5 (signal subscription dispatch). Signals must be stored before they can be subscribed to.; AUDIT-TYPE-007: HarvestCandidate could benefit from lifecycle typestate (Proposed/Evaluated/Accepted/Rejected). PROBLEM: harvest.rs:61 HarvestCandidate is a single struct with mutable status field. Candidates go through states: proposed → evaluated → accepted/rejected → transacted. The crystallization_guard() checks status at runtime. Confidence: 0.5 — this is a nice-to-have for type safety, not a correctness issue. SOLUTION: Consider HarvestCandidate<Proposed>/HarvestCandidate<Evaluated> typestate to make commit step type-safe. VERIFICATION: Cannot call commit on HarvestCandidate<Proposed> (compile error). DEPENDS-ON: W2-006 (crystallization guard). INTERACTS-WITH: None.; AUDIT-EXT ARCH-001 (from AUDIT_REPORT): bootstrap_hypotheses.rs performs filesystem I/O in kernel — violates kernel's own 'no IO' contract. PROBLEM: bootstrap_hypotheses.rs:11,133,193,224,326,362,412-443 uses std::fs::read_dir, std::fs::write, std::fs::create_dir_all, std::fs::remove_file. The kernel crate's lib.rs:8 declares 'no IO, no filesystem access.' This module violates the declaration. JUSTIFICATION: The kernel's purity guarantee is load-bearing — it enables deterministic testing, property-based verification, and Kani proofs. A module that performs filesystem IO cannot be property-tested reliably (tests depend on filesystem state). Additionally, this is a C8 violation — the module detects specific project types (Cargo.toml, go.mod, package.json) which is domain-specific behavior. SOLUTION: Move to CLI crate. Kernel receives filesystem scan results as data (e.g., Vec<ProjectMarker>). The CLI performs the scan and passes results in. VERIFICATION: grep 'std::fs' crates/braid-kernel/src/ returns zero results (currently returns matches in bootstrap_hypotheses.rs). DEPENDENCIES: Independent. FILES: crates/braid-kernel/src/bootstrap_hypotheses.rs. SEVERITY: High (contract violation). WAVE: 1. EFFORT: 3h.; META-1: Type 9 divergence — the system cannot diagnose its own failure to converge [STRATEGIC, from PROJECT_ASSESSMENT deepest question + meta-analysis synthesis]. The project claims to implement observe-compare-reduce at every level. But the systems most important discrepancy — F(S) stagnant at 0.62 for 13 sessions, hypothesis ledger degrading, 265 untested INVs accumulating — is not detected, diagnosed, or reduced by the system itself. A human reading braid status sees the numbers. But the guidance system does not emit your verification pipeline is the bottleneck. The routing function does not prioritize verification over features when spec-impl gap widens. The harvest does not capture F(S) hasnt moved in 5 sessions as anomalous. If Braid is truly a learning system, it should detect its own stagnation and recommend the verification sprint. The fact that it takes external audits to identify the obvious means the self-improvement loop (Y-combinator property) is not yet operational. SOLUTION: Add stagnation detection to methodology.rs: when F(S) delta across last N sessions is below threshold epsilon, generate a high-urgency signal :signal/type :reflexive with recommendation to shift from feature building to verification. Wire this signal into routing with 2x priority boost for verification tasks. VERIFICATION: Run braid status on a store where F(S) hasnt moved in 5 sessions. Verify guidance output recommends verification sprint. DEPENDENCIES: Depends on OPEN-LOOP-4 (signals must be stored as datoms) and AUDIT-COH-5 (signal dispatch must be wired). This is the capstone — it validates the self-improvement thesis.; C8-EXT-1: INNATE_CONCEPTS constant hardcodes domain-specific concept seeds [MEDIUM C8, from FULL_AUDIT F-C8-005]. concept.rs:1362-1383 defines 5 bootstrap concepts: components, dependencies, invariants, patterns, anomalies. The invariants concept name is DDIS-specific. Others are reasonably generic. Test at line 2425 confirms count is 5. SOLUTION: Load innate concepts from policy manifest instead of const array. DDIS manifest provides invariants; research manifest provides hypotheses. VERIFICATION: INNATE_CONCEPTS removed from kernel. Custom policy manifest with different seed concepts produces different initial clusters. DEPENDENCIES: Part of C8 migration. Low priority within C8 work. ~2 hours.; AUDIT-COH-2: 42 reverse-gap invariants exist in code but not in spec/ directory. Implementation has crystallized invariants that lack formal specification: INV-TASK-001..006 (task management: status monotonicity, DAG acyclicity, ready computation, priority ordering, spec anchoring, completion evidence -- 70 tests, no formal spec). INV-FOUNDATION-006..014 (bedrock principles including C8 substrate independence -- referenced in CLAUDE.md but not in spec/). INV-QUERY-025..034 (extended graph algorithms beyond the 24 specified -- 90 tests). INV-EMBEDDING-001..004, INV-PROMOTE-001..004, INV-HARVEST-010..012 (subsystem invariants). These represent implementation that has drifted ahead of specification -- C5 traceability requires spec elements for all implementation artifacts. SOLUTION: Crystallize these 42 invariants into formal spec elements in spec/ files. Priority: INV-TASK-* first (core workflow, heavily tested), then INV-FOUNDATION-* (bedrock principles). VERIFICATION: After crystallization, braid trace should show increased coverage. No gaps between code references and spec elements. DEPENDENCIES: Independent. Can be done in parallel with any other work.; AUDIT-EXT SCOPE-CREEP (from PROJECT_ASSESSMENT Section 5): Phase C/D features being built while Phase B incomplete — scope creep diagnosis. PROBLEM: Sessions 044-046 added concept engine (198 KB), inquiry engine, online calibration, and PERF-REGRESSION epic — all Phase C/D features. Meanwhile: hypothesis ledger degrading (mean error 0.521), 265 INVs untested, F(S) hasn't moved in 13 sessions, DOGFOOD-2 scored 3.48/10. The project is building intelligence features on top of uncalibrated infrastructure. Velocity stall: 0 issues closed in last 7 days (was 133/week). Issue inflation: 883 total (70 open across 8+ epics across 4 phases). JUSTIFICATION: ADR-FOUNDATION-014 (convergence thesis) says every change must close a loop, not open one. Building Phase C/D features when Phase B has known structural cracks (open calibration loop, untested INVs, degrading hypothesis accuracy) opens loops. The atomic operation — observe reality, compare to model, reduce discrepancy — is being applied to new subsystems before existing subsystems converge. This is the build-floors-3-5-while-floor-2-has-cracks pattern. SOLUTION: PROJECT_ASSESSMENT's recommendation: stop building new intelligence features, fix calibration pipeline, verify existing 265 INVs, prove saw-tooth convergence works. If F(S) reaches 0.78 through verification alone, the architecture is vindicated. If it can't, something deeper is wrong. VERIFICATION: F(S) movement after verification sprint. No new spec elements added for 5 sessions. DEPENDENCIES: Strategic guidance. Informs prioritization of all other findings. FINDING SOURCE: PROJECT_ASSESSMENT.md Sections 5-6. SEVERITY: High (strategic).; META-3: Core hypothesis (harvest/seed transforms workflow) unvalidated after 46 sessions [STRATEGIC, from PROJECT_ASSESSMENT roadmap critique]. S0 success criterion: work 25 turns, harvest, start fresh with seed — new session picks up without manual re-explanation. Target was 1-2 weeks; its been 46 sessions over 5 weeks. DOGFOOD-2 on external Go project scored 3.48/10. The project has been building intelligence features (concept engine, inquiry engine, online calibration, topology) while the foundational hypothesis remains unproven on external data. SOLUTION: Define and execute S0 validation mechanically: (1) Select external project (non-Rust, non-DDIS). (2) Work 25 turns with braid observe/harvest/seed. (3) Harvest and start completely fresh session with seed only. (4) Score: can the new session continue without manual re-explanation? Rigorous scoring rubric. VERIFICATION: Numerical score on the rubric. Target: above 7/10. If below 5/10, diagnose whether problem is seed assembly, harvest quality, or the concept itself. DEPENDENCIES: Should happen AFTER AUDIT-SOUND-1 (coherence gate) and AUDIT-SOUND-3 (hypothesis fix) so the system is operating correctly when tested. ~2 sessions.; AUDIT-EXT F-CORR-001 (from AUDIT_REPORT): No causally_independent() implementation — conflict predicate is unsound. PROBLEM: Zero matches for 'causally_independent' or 'causal_ancestor' in entire kernel. resolution.rs:225-238 has_conflict() does not check causal independence. Sequential single-agent updates are incorrectly flagged as conflicts. Multi-agent causal chains will be misclassified. INV-STORE-010 and INV-RESOLUTION-004 conditions 5-6 require causal independence checking. JUSTIFICATION: The conflict predicate is the foundation of the resolution system. Without causal independence checking, every pair of assertions on the same (entity, attribute) from the same agent in different transactions is classified as a conflict, even when one causally follows the other. This produces false positives that overwhelm the resolution pipeline. SOLUTION: Implement is_causal_ancestor(store, tx1, tx2) via BFS over :tx/causal-predecessors. Wire into has_conflict() as condition 6. VERIFICATION: Two sequential assertions by same agent on same (e,a) with causal link are NOT flagged as conflict. DEPENDENCIES: Independent. Improves resolution accuracy which feeds into F(S) K component. FILES: crates/braid-kernel/src/resolution.rs:225-238. SEVERITY: High. WAVE: 1. EFFORT: 4h.; Store health check — verifying observe works after txn corruption fix.; AUDIT-EXT ARCH-002 (from AUDIT_REPORT): SystemTime::now() in 10+ kernel functions