C-002]. Spec files contain 201-216 INVs by manual count. braid status reports 265 current-stage INVs untested. The discrepancy (265 vs 216) suggests either: (1) spec elements created via braid spec create that dont exist in spec/*.md files, or (2) the current-stage filter includes future-stage elements. The store and spec files are not in exact correspondence — this is a bilateral coherence violation (store has elements spec files dont, or vice versa). SOLUTION: Run braid query to get exact store count of invariant entities. Reconcile with spec/*.md files. Document discrepancies. If store has extra, either add to spec or mark as superseded. If spec has extra, transact into store. VERIFICATION: Store INV count matches spec file count within documented variance. DEPENDENCIES: Independent. ~2 hours.; SPEC-GAP-2: 123 observations with uncrystallized spec IDs [MEDIUM, from FULL_AUDIT F-SPEC-003 + braid status methodology gaps]. 123 observations reference non-existent spec elements — forward references to spec IDs never formalized. Also 28 tasks with unresolved spec refs. These are knowledge artifacts referencing phantoms, violating C5 (traceability). The observation-to-spec pipeline stalls at the crystallize step. SOLUTION: Batch crystallize: for each phantom spec ID, either create the spec element via braid spec create or update the observation to remove the phantom reference. Target: uncrystallized count below 20. VERIFICATION: braid status methodology gaps shows fewer than 20 uncrystallized observations. DEPENDENCIES: Related to AUDIT-COH-2 (42 reverse-gap invariants) — both are spec-impl alignment issues. Independent execution.; CORR-5: Value::Ref admits unvalidated reference cycles and dangling refs [MEDIUM, from FULL_AUDIT F-TYPE-002]. Value::Ref(EntityId) allows any EntityId as reference target including entities that do not exist in the store. Schema validation checks value types but not referential integrity. This is intentional for eventual consistency (C4 — re